  "prompt": "What is Karl Marx's economy or Marxism in a simple way?",
  "response": "Karl Marx's economic theory, or Marxism, can be explained simply as follows:\n\n1. Class Struggle\n- Society is divided into two main classes: the bourgeoisie (owners of production) and the proletariat (workers)\n- The bourgeoisie exploits the proletariat by making profits from their labor\n\n2. Capitalism's Flaws\n- Capitalism creates inequality\n- Workers are paid less than the value they produce\n- Wealth accumulates with the owners, not the workers\n\n3. Key Concepts\n- Workers should own the means of production\n- Economic system should be based on collective ownership\n- Goal is to create a classless society where resources are distributed fairly\n\n4. Economic Stages\n- Marx believed societies progress through stages:\n  - Primitive communism\n  - Slave society\n  - Feudalism\n  - Capitalism\n  - Socialism\n  - Communism (final stage with no social classes)\n\n5. Ultimate Vision\n- Eliminate private property\n- Ensure equal economic opportunities\n- Create a society where everyone contributes and benefits equally\n\nIn essence, Marxism critiques capitalism and proposes a more equitable economic system where workers have control and wealth is shared more evenly.",
